</div><div class="info-panel__citations info-panel__item"><a href="#tab-citations" class="btn btn--inverse btn--slim" data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="View Citations" aria-label="View Citations"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-format_quote"></i></a></div><div class="info-panel__formats info-panel__item"><a href="#core-collateral-purchase-access" class="btn btn--access" data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="Go to purchase options" aria-label="Go to purchase options"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-lock-open"></i><span class="link-text">Get Access</span></a></div></div></div></div></header><div data-core-nav="header" data-extent="frontmatter"><div class="core-nav-wrapper core-container" aria-label="Article navigation"><div><button aria-controls="article_sections_menu" aria-expanded="false" aria-label="Toggle section navigation menu"><i class="icon-list" aria-hidden="true"></i><span>Contents</span></button><nav id="article_sections_menu" aria-label="Contents" data-core-nav="article"><ul><li><a href="#abstract">Abstract</a></li><li><a href="#core-sec-figures">Figures</a></li><li><a href="#bibliography">References</a></li></ul></nav></div><nav id="article_collateral_menu"><ul class="collateral-pill" data-core-nav="collateral"><li><a href="#core-collateral-info" aria-controls="core-collateral-info" aria-disabled="true" disabled="true" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="left" data-original-title="Information & Authors" title="Information & Authors" aria-expanded="false"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-info"></i><span class="sr-only">Information & Authors</span></a></li><li><a href="#core-collateral-metrics" aria-controls="core-collateral-metrics" aria-disabled="true" disabled="true" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="left" data-original-title="Metrics & Citations" title="Metrics & Citations" aria-expanded="false"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-metrics"></i><span class="sr-only">Metrics & Citations</span></a></li><li><a href="#core-collateral-purchase-access" aria-controls="core-collateral-purchase-access" aria-disabled="true" disabled="true" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="left" data-original-title="Get Access" title="Get Access" aria-expanded="false"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-lock-open"></i><span class="sr-only">Get Access</span></a></li><li><a href="#core-collateral-references" aria-controls="core-collateral-references" aria-disabled="true" disabled="true" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="left" data-original-title="References" title="References" aria-expanded="false"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-references"></i><span class="sr-only">References</span></a></li><li><a href="#core-collateral-figures" aria-controls="core-collateral-figures" aria-disabled="true" disabled="true" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="left" data-original-title="Figures" title="Figures" aria-expanded="false"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-photo"></i><span class="sr-only">Figures</span></a></li><li><a href="#core-collateral-tables" aria-controls="core-collateral-tables" aria-disabled="true" disabled="true" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="left" data-original-title="Tables" title="Tables" aria-expanded="false"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-table"></i><span class="sr-only">Tables</span></a></li><li><a href="#core-collateral-media" aria-controls="core-collateral-media" aria-disabled="true" disabled="true" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="left" data-original-title="Media" title="Media" aria-expanded="false"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-play-circle-filled"></i><span class="sr-only">Media</span></a></li><li><a href="#core-collateral-share" aria-controls="core-collateral-share" aria-disabled="true" disabled="true" data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="left" data-original-title="Share" title="Share" aria-expanded="false"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-share"></i><span class="sr-only">Share</span></a></li></ul></nav></div></div><div data-core-wrapper="content"><div id="abstracts" data-extent="frontmatter"><div class="core-container"><section id="abstract" property="abstract" typeof="Text" role="doc-abstract"><h2 property="name">Abstract</h2><div role="paragraph">The population of adults with repaired tetralogy of Fallot (TOF) is growing, thanks to improvements in the surgical and medical management of this condition. Accordingly, late postrepair complications are important medical concerns in these individuals. Initial surgical repair of TOF typically occurs in infancy, consisting of patch repair of the ventricular septal defect (VSD) and relief of right ventricular outflow tract (RVOT) obstruction. Although patients may remain asymptomatic for several decades, the majority will have progressive pulmonic regurgitation that leads to right ventricular (RV) dilatation and functional deterioration. Other frequently seen complications include branch pulmonary artery stenosis, RVOT aneurysms, and recurrent VSDs. Cardiac computed tomography (CT) is widely available and, in some cases, is the imaging modality of choice for serial evaluation of TOF patients. CT is particularly useful when magnetic resonance (MR) imaging is contraindicated (eg, in patients with implantable cardiac devices). Unlike MR imaging, cardiac CT allows excellent visualization of endovascular stents and stent-mounted valves. Retrospective electrocardiographically gated cardiac CT can be used for accurate volumetric and functional analysis of the RV. Comprehensive serial evaluation will assist in determining the need for surgical pulmonary valve repair in the setting of progressive RV dysfunction. Three-dimensional volumetric images are useful for evaluation of stent integrity and aneurysm formation. The radiologist should be familiar with the anatomy of TOF, surgical interventions for repair, and postrepair complications encountered at follow-up imaging of these patients. By extracting the breadth of information obtained with cardiac multidetector CT, the radiologist can play an essential role in the management of adult patients with repaired TOF.</div><div role="paragraph">© RSNA, 2013</div></section></div></div><section id="bodymatter" data-extent="bodymatter" property="articleBody" typeof="Text"><div class="core-container"><section aria-labelledby="denial-block-title" class="denial-block "><h2 id="denial-block-title" class="denial-block__title">Get full access to this article</h2><p class="denial-block__text">View all available purchase options and get full access to this article.</p><div class="denial-block__cta"><a href="#core-collateral-purchase-access" class="btn btn--access"><i aria-hidden="true" class="icon-lock-open"></i><span>Get Access</span></a></div><footer class="denial-block__footer"><span>Already a Subscriber? </span><span>Sign in as an </span><a href="/action/showLogin?redirectUri=/doi/10.1148/rg.334125114">individual</a><span> or via your </span><a href="/action/ssostart?uri=/doi/10.1148/rg.334125114">institution</a></footer></section></div></section><section id="backmatter" data-extent="backmatter"><div class="core-container"><section id="core-sec-figures" data-type="figures"><h2>Figures</h2><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig01a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.334125114/asset/images/large/125114fig01a.jpeg" height="605" width="798" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 1a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.334125114&amp;id=fig01a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig01b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.334125114/asset/images/large/125114fig01b.jpeg" height="687" width="805" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 1b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.334125114&amp;id=fig01b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig01c" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.334125114/asset/images/large/125114fig01c.jpeg" height="687" width="770" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 1c</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.334125114&amp;id=fig01c">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig01d" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.334125114/asset/images/large/125114fig01d.jpeg" height="638" width="758" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 1d</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.334125114&amp;id=fig01d">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig01e" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.334125114/asset/images/large/125114fig01e.jpeg" height="638" width="817" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 1e</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.334125114&amp;id=fig01e">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig01f" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.334125114/asset/images/large/125114fig01f.jpeg" height="695" width="783" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 1f</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.334125114&amp;id=fig01f">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig01g" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.334125114/asset/images/large/125114fig01g.jpeg" height="695" width="792" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 1g</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.334125114&amp;id=fig01g">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig02" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.334125114/asset/images/large/125114fig02.jpeg" height="743" width="800" aria-labelledby="fig02" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 2</span> Axial oblique CT angiographic image obtained in a 9-year-old boy with TOF demonstrates an anomalous left CA (arrowheads) arising from the right cusp and coursing anterior to the proximal main pulmonary artery <i>(MPA)</i>. <i>Ao</i> = aorta, <i>RPA</i> = right pulmonary artery.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.334125114&amp;id=fig02">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig03" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.334125114/asset/images/large/125114fig03.jpeg" height="690" width="800" aria-labelledby="fig03" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 3</span> Coronal oblique VR CT angiographic image obtained in a 5-week-old boy with TOF and complete pulmonary artery stenosis (PAS) shows three major aorticopulmonary collateral arteries (arrowheads) arising from the undersurface of the aortic arch and the anterior descending thoracic aorta <i>(Ao)</i>. A unifocalization procedure was subsequently performed prior to definitive repair to bring these vessels into continuity with the branch PAs.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.334125114&amp;id=fig03">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig04a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.334125114/asset/images/large/125114fig04a.jpeg" height="704" width="822" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 4a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.334125114&amp;id=fig04a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig04b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.334125114/asset/images/large/125114fig04b.jpeg" height="704" width="853" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 4b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.334125114&amp;id=fig04b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig05a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.334125114/asset/images/large/125114fig05a.jpeg" height="788" width="782" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 5a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.334125114&amp;id=fig05a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig05b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.334125114/asset/images/large/125114fig05b.jpeg" height="585" width="793" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 5b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.334125114&amp;id=fig05b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig06" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.334125114/asset/images/large/125114fig06.jpeg" height="840" width="800" aria-labelledby="fig06" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 6</span> Sagittal VR CT image obtained in a 12-year-old boy who had undergone remote transannular repair of TOF shows a markedly enlarged main PA (arrowheads) and a bulging RVOT (arrow), findings that are compatible with an aneurysm.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.334125114&amp;id=fig06">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig07a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.334125114/asset/images/large/125114fig07a.jpeg" height="780" width="856" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 7a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.334125114&amp;id=fig07a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig07b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.334125114/asset/images/large/125114fig07b.jpeg" height="780" width="819" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 7b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.334125114&amp;id=fig07b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig08" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.334125114/asset/images/large/125114fig08.jpeg" height="814" width="850" aria-labelledby="fig08" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 8</span> Coronal oblique MIP CT image obtained in a 5-month-old boy with TOF and a right-sided Blalock-Taussig shunt (arrow) demonstrates stenosis of the right pulmonary artery <i>(RPA)</i> near the shunt anastomosis (arrowheads), a common complication in these patients. <i>Ao</i> = aorta, <i>LPA</i> = left pulmonary artery, <i>RA</i> = right atrium.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.334125114&amp;id=fig08">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig09a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.334125114/asset/images/large/125114fig09a.jpeg" height="734" width="830" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 9a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.334125114&amp;id=fig09a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig09b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.334125114/asset/images/large/125114fig09b.jpeg" height="734" width="844" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 9b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.334125114&amp;id=fig09b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig10a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.334125114/asset/images/large/125114fig10a.jpeg" height="730" width="778" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 10a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.334125114&amp;id=fig10a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig10b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.334125114/asset/images/large/125114fig10b.jpeg" height="730" width="797" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 10b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.334125114&amp;id=fig10b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig11a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.334125114/asset/images/large/125114fig11a.jpeg" height="745" width="788" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 11a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.334125114&amp;id=fig11a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig11b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.334125114/asset/images/large/125114fig11b.jpeg" height="745" width="787" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 11b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.334125114&amp;id=fig11b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig12a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.334125114/asset/images/large/125114fig12a.jpeg" height="717" width="772" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 12a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.334125114&amp;id=fig12a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig12b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.334125114/asset/images/large/125114fig12b.jpeg" height="717" width="803" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 12b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.334125114&amp;id=fig12b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig13" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.334125114/asset/images/large/125114fig13.jpeg" height="695" width="850" aria-labelledby="fig13" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 13</span> Axial VR CT image obtained in a 12-year-old girl with TOF and bilateral branch PAS who had undergone placement of a stent in the left PA and of a stent-mounted replacement PV clearly demonstrates mild compression of the proximal portion of the stent (arrowheads) as it passes behind the aorta (arrow).<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.334125114&amp;id=fig13">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig14a" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.334125114/asset/images/large/125114fig14a.jpeg" height="744" width="859" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 14a</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.334125114&amp;id=fig14a">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig14b" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.334125114/asset/images/large/125114fig14b.jpeg" height="744" width="816" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 14b</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.334125114&amp;id=fig14b">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div><div class="figure-wrap"><figure id="fig14c" class="graphic"><img src="/cms/10.1148/rg.334125114/asset/images/large/125114fig14c.jpeg" height="690" width="850" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 14c</span> <!-- There is no content. --><div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.334125114&amp;id=fig14c">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div></section><section id="bibliography" role="doc-bibliography"><h2>References</h2><div role="list"><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">1.</div><div id="r1" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Kalra N, Klewer SE, Raasch H, Sorrell VL. Update on tetralogy of Fallot for the adult cardiologist including a brief historical and surgical perspective. <em>Congenit Heart Dis</em> 2010;5(3):208–219.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1747-0803.2010.00402.x">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/20576040/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Update+on+tetralogy+of+Fallot+for+the+adult+cardiologist+including+a+brief+historical+and+surgical+perspective&amp;author=N+Kalra&amp;author=SE+Klewer&amp;author=H+Raasch&amp;author=VL+Sorrell&amp;publication_year=2010&amp;journal=Congenit+Heart+Dis&amp;pages=208-219&amp;doi=10.1111%2Fj.1747-0803.2010.00402.x&amp;pmid=20576040">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">2.</div><div id="r2" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Norton KI, Tong C, Glass RB, Nielsen JC. Cardiac MR imaging assessment following tetralogy of Fallot repair. <em>RadioGraphics</em> 2006;26(1):197–211.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1148/rg.261055064">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/16418252/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Cardiac+MR+imaging+assessment+following+tetralogy+of+Fallot+repair&amp;author=KI+Norton&amp;author=C+Tong&amp;author=RB+Glass&amp;author=JC+Nielsen&amp;publication_year=2006&amp;journal=RadioGraphics&amp;pages=197-211&amp;doi=10.1148%2Frg.261055064&amp;pmid=16418252">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">3.</div><div id="r3" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Nollert G, Fischlein T, Bouterwek S, Böhmer C, Klinner W, Reichart B. Long-term survival in patients with repair of tetralogy of Fallot: 36-year follow-up of 490 survivors of the first year after surgical repair. <em>J Am Coll Cardiol</em> 1997;30(5):1374–1383.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/S0735-1097(97)00318-5">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/9350942/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Long-term+survival+in+patients+with+repair+of+tetralogy+of+Fallot%3A+36-year+follow-up+of+490+survivors+of+the+first+year+after+surgical+repair&amp;author=G+Nollert&amp;author=T+Fischlein&amp;author=S+Bouterwek&amp;author=C+B%C3%B6hmer&amp;author=W+Klinner&amp;author=B+Reichart&amp;publication_year=1997&amp;journal=J+Am+Coll+Cardiol&amp;pages=1374-1383&amp;doi=10.1016%2FS0735-1097%2897%2900318-5&amp;pmid=9350942">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div